      <p>Behind-the-ear (BTE) models are usually best for children due to safety and adaptability, while completely-in-canal devices are more discreet and suitable for adults with mild loss. 
      (<a href="https://www.together.stjude.org" target="_blank">St. Jude</a>, <a href="https://www.mayoclinic.org" target="_blank">Mayo Clinic</a>)</p>
    
